<br>
Every time you add a regulation, someone or thing has to be in place to monitor compliance and punish disobediance.  Taken to an absurd extreme, VI could ensure compliance with the EULA by controlling all guilds through VI employee leadership of each one.  But then again, where is the fun there?  Where is there room for creativity in that set up?  How much would that cost?<br>
<br>
I do think the idea (may have been yours) to /ignore GUILD &quot;00ber D00ds&quot; is good, and consideration should be made to try to implement that command.  However, I can't see any need for tougher standards to form a guild.<br>
<br>
I do believe the guild wipe system is a subprogram that compares the requirements to have an active guild vs. the guild's enrollment.  No big need for oversight there.<br>
<br>
Maedhros<br>
Druid, 3rd Circle<br>
